'''Business identification number''' or '''BIN''' is a proposed identification number to replace eighteen different registration numbers required to be obtained by a company to operate in [[India]].

==Details==
Business identification number or BIN is a proposed identification number to replace eighteen different registration numbers required to be obtained by a company to operate in [[India]].<ref>{{citation |title=Government to improve ease of doing business; to introduce Business Identification Number for companies |url=http://economictimes.com/news/economy/policy/government-to-improve-ease-of-doing-business-to-introduce-business-identification-number-for-companies/articleshow/50963352.cms |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=12 February 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Ease of doing biz: Govt to soon introduce Business Identification Number for companies |url=http://wap.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/govt-to-soon-introduce-business-identification-number-for-cos-116021200879_1.html |work=[[Business Standard]] |date=12 February 2016 }}</ref> The [[Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation]] is looking at allotting a 16-digit number to each business establishment. Apart from helping the government create and maintain a comprehensive database on businesses, the unique number will also simplify a business' dealings with various governmental agencies by reducing chances of duplicate entities, resolving identity issues and saving time when going for future registrations or licences.<ref>{{citation |title=On Aadhaar's lines: Now, unique identity number for businesses on cards |url=http://economictimes.com/news/economy/policy/on-aadhaars-lines-now-unique-identity-number-for-businesses-on-cards/articleshow/51655321.cms |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=2 April 2016 }}</ref>

