{{Infobox brand | name = Energen | logo = | logo_upright = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | image = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | producttype = Cereal Drink | currentowner = PT [[Mayora Indah]] Tbk. | producedby = | country = Indonesia | introduced = {{Start date and age|1992}} | related = | markets = Philippines, Indonesia | previousowners = | trademarkregistrations = | ambassadors = | tagline = | website = }}
'''Energen''' is a [[Drink mix|cereal drink]] brand<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/health-and-family/2012/11/27/874201/hearty-healthy-breakfast-kids|title=A hearty, healthy breakfast for kids|newspaper=philstar.com|access-date=2016-12-03}}</ref> owned by PT [[Mayora Indah]] and the Philippines-based Ecossential Foods Corporation. This brand was fortified with SIGMAvit.
== History ==
=== Indonesia === In 1992, Energen was introduced by PT [[Mayora Indah]] Tbk. with the flavors [[Vanilla]], [[Chocolate]], [[Corn]], [[Green bean|Green Beans]] and [[Ginger]].
===Philippines === In 2008, Energen was introduced by Ecossential Foods Corporation with the flavors [[Vanilla]], [[Chocolate]], and [[Ginger]]. It was followed by [[Nestlé Bear Brand|Bear Brand Busog Lusog]] in May, 2008. In 2010, [[Monggo (vegetable)|Monggo]] flavor was introduced, but in 2013 it was discontinued, but remains available in Indonesia.
== Variants == Energen is enriched with SIGMAVit with [[milk]], [[malt]], [[cereal]] and [[oats]]. In [[Indonesia]], it was manufactured as oat milk (like [[Quaker Oats]]). In the [[Philippines]], it was manufactured as a mixture of oat drink and real [[fruit]] called Energen Go-Fruit in 2014, though it was discontinued in 2015.
