{{Infobox person | image =Afbeelding2-daleboudt-goldschmeding.jpg | image_size = | name = Frits Goldschmeding | caption =Founders Ger Daleboudt and Frits Goldschmeding (r) eight years after starting their company | birth_name = | birth_date = {{bya|1933}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Dutch | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = Amsterdam, Netherlands | education = | alma mater = [[VU University Amsterdam]] | occupation = Investor and academic | known for = Founder, [[Randstad Holding]] | salary = | networth = [[United States dollar|$]]4.0 billion (January 2015)<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Frits Goldschmeding|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/frits-goldschmeding/#|website=Forbes|accessdate=24 January 2015}}</ref> | spouse = | parents = | children = 3 | relatives = | website = }}
'''Frits Goldschmeding''' (born 1933) is a Dutch businessman, founder of [[Randstad Holding]], the world's largest staffing company.
==Early life== Goldschmeding was born in 1933, and has a doctorate from the [[VU University Amsterdam]].<ref name=Forbes/>
==Career== He founded Uitzendbureau Amstelveen in 1960, and in 1964 renamed it [[Randstad Holding|Randstad]].<ref name=Forbes/> Goldschmeding took Randstad public in 1990, and in 2008, merged it with the Dutch group Vedior. According to ''[[Forbes]]'', Goldschmeding has a 35% stake in the company, and a net worth of $4.5 billion, as of November 2017.<ref name=Forbes/>
Goldschmeding was also a professor at the Centre for Entrepreneurship at [[Nyenrode Business University]].<ref name=Forbes/>
==Personal life== Goldschmeding is married, has three children and lives in Amsterdam, Netherlands.<ref name=Forbes/>
