'''[[Ratu]] Jone Yavala Kubuabola''' (11 September 1946 – 16 September 2018) was a Fijian politician. He was the country's [[Minister for Finance (Fiji)|Minister for Finance]] from 2000 until the government was deposed in the [[2006 Fijian coup d'état|military coup of 5 December 2006]]. He also represented the [[South West Urban (Fijian Communal Constituency, Fiji)|South West Urban]] [[Fijians|Fijian]] [[Communal constituencies]] in the [[House of Representatives of Fiji|House of Representatives]], to which he was [[Fijian general election, 2001|elected]] as a candidate of the ''[[Soqosoqo Duavata ni Lewenivanua]]'' (SDL) in 2001. He retained his seat in the [[Fijian general election, 2006|general election of 2006]]. He later helped set up the [[Social Democratic Liberal Party]] (SODELPA). He died on 16 September 2018 at age 72.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Conduit |first1=Rox |title=Leader of Opposition laments passing of Ratu Jone Kubuabola|url=http://www.fbc.com.fj/fiji/68638/leader-of-opposition-laments-passing-of-ratu-jone-kubuabola- |accessdate=17 September 2018 |work=FBC News}}</ref> Prior to his career in politics he was governor of the [[Reserve Bank of Fiji]].<ref>[http://www.fijitimes.com/ratu-jone-kubuabola-passes-away/ Ratu Jone Kubuabola passes away]. Fiji Times. Retrieved 17 September 2018.</ref> He was the older brother to [[Inoke Kubuabola]], another government minister.
